Summary of Limitations:
Max number of partitions: Up to 4,000 partitions for date/timestamp or integer partitioning.
Partition granularity: Can only partition by DATE, TIMESTAMP, DATETIME, or INTEGER.
Partition scan limit: Up to 1,000 partitions can be scanned per query.
Expiration limits: Partition expiration can only be set for the entire table (up to 30,000 days).
NULL values: May cause issues with partitioning and need to be handled carefully.
Performance overhead: Partitioning may be inefficient for small tables.
Partitioning cannot be modified: You cannot change partitioning after creating the table.
BigQuery creates an unnamed partition (also called the __UNPARTITIONED__ partition) to store this data.can contain NULL data as well
only one column can be used for partitioning a table at a time.
Clustering: Up to 4 clustering columns can be used alongside partitioning




