What Are BigQuery Reservations?
Slots:
Slots are the basic unit of compute capacity in BigQuery. Each slot is a virtual CPU that can process data in parallel.
By default, BigQuery uses on-demand pricing, where slots are shared across all users in a multi-tenant environment. This can lead to variable performance during peak usage times.
Reservations:
Reservations allow you to purchase and allocate a fixed number of slots exclusively for your organization or specific projects.
With reservations, you can ensure consistent performance for critical workloads and avoid contention with other users.
Commitments:
Reservations are tied to slot commitments, which are purchased for a specific duration (e.g., 1 year or 3 years) at a discounted rate compared to on-demand pricing.

